The paper focuses on designing an AI agent to assist human users in completing a task while keeping their cognitive load low. This suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific task domain is collaborative packing, which involves a robotic manipulator, indicating a potential connection to robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the development of a framework to predict and manipulate human decision making, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
